\mt2 The first letter from
\mt1 Simon вҖҳthe RockвҖҷ (Peter)
\is1 Introduction
\ip \bk The first letter from Simon вҖҳPeterвҖҷ\bk* was written to believers scattered throughout Asia Minor (also called Anatolia, now part of modern Turkey). Peter wrote to encourage the believers that it's necessary for them to be strong even in the middle of much persecution that comes because of their faith in the messiah. He reminds them about their salvation, the death of Yeshua the messiah, and of his coming back to life. Because Peter told them that there must always remember their hope in heaven, then they can persevere even through all the difficulties here on earth. He also reminds them that if their faith holds strong through their suffering of difficulties and persecutions, they will receive a gift at вҖңThe time when Yeshua the messiah is revealed.вҖқ (1:7,13)
\ip He also warns them that it's necessary to watch their behaviour as followers of the messiah and it's necessary that they follow the guidance of their elders.
\iot Main components of Peter's letter
\io1 Introduction \ior 1:1-2\ior*
\io1 The reminder about the future benefits of salvation \ior 1:3-12\ior*
\io1 Encouragement about godly living \ior 1:13вҖ“2:10\ior*
\io1 Respecting those who have authority over us \ior 2:11вҖ“3:7\ior*
\io1 Advice concerning the coming persecutions \ior 3:8вҖ“4:19\ior*
\io1 Advice for teachers and believers \ior 5:1-11\ior*
\io1 Farewell \ior 5:12-14\ior*
